<script language="JavaScript"><!--
var date = new Date();
var d  = date.getDate();
var day = (d < 10) ? '0' + d : d;
var m = date.getMonth() + 1;
var month = (m < 10) ? '0' + m : m;
var yy = date.getYear();
var year = (yy < 1000) ? yy + 1900 : yy;

document.write(day + "/" + month + "/" + year);
//--></script>

it's my first day back at work after taking november off.  i guess it's good to be back.  there's not much to do other than catch up on email and surf the web for a little bit.  i'm still recovering from the flu i had last week;  despite my constant hacking, people have been coming by to visit with me in my cube.  i guess they've missed me :)

oh and i also got a free slice of cheese from the cafe upstairs that usually charges way too much for their sandwiches.  the cheese was pretty tasty too.

it's only 3:30 but i feel so drained by the day already.  maybe i'll head home a little earlier today.

what a horrible movie... i made the boys watch it last night on tnt.  sorry guys!

but i just realized that i'm only going to be in the office for only one day in november!!

gonna do a bit of traveling very soon.  my first business trip overseas to amsterdam from end of october to november.  then off to philly for a wedding and my first authentic cheesesteak!  then i'm taking a bit of comp time and might go to visit a friend in oxford.  not sure if i want to go to europe two times in one month, so we'll see how that goes.

so much for getting smiley a baby brother... a nice guy from shiba inu rescue is on his way over right now to come see little hiro and find him a new home.  the past week has been a tough one for the little guy.  like any puppy, he gets upset when i leave him home alone during the day, and he sorta goes crazy when i come home.  we had a scary incident with the couch the other night... :(

so shiba rescue is taking the little critter away and doing all of us a favor.
holy crap... macr stock keeps climbing up this morning.

eating an oatmeal pecan chocolate chip cookie right now :) i think ivana is trying to fatten me up! she baked me a dozen of these last night. took muni for the first time in a long time this morning. i can't believe they are going to raise the adult fare to $1.25... i'm glad i still look young enough to pay the youth fare which will remain at $0.35 :D

today we had a pizza party to welcome back our old admin from maternity leave and to say farewell to her temp replacement. it wasn't sad though because the temp is going to become a full time admin for another group in the company :) i ate sooo much of the mitchell's ice cream. then sometime after lunch someone kidnapped the team puppy and fedex'ed its left ear to my manager.

i have two weeks of vacation coming up this fall, and i can't think of anywhere to go by myself.

i'm thinking about new york and boston since i have friends out there.  not too exciting though. :P

any ideas?

my netgear wireless router finally arrived today.  it was only $30 or so after some rebate and amazon gold box coupon :)  i just set it up, and it was a breeze.  vpn works, and the connection is so fast.  i never have to leave my bed again!

i think i've been anxious recently about not having enough time to do stuff.  working every saturday is really wearing me out, and i haven't had time to do laundry in 3 weeks.  it was getting pretty bad, but i finally managed to throw it into the washer tonight.  maybe i'll have time to dry tomorrow.

at least we got to watch some fun tv tonight.  queer eye for the straight guy is hilarious.  i love the cute blonde who picks out a new wardrobe for the straight guy.  i want his job!  he does indeed look a lot like ellen.  anyways, it's a fun show, and we saw two episodes tonight :)

as i drifted into consciousness this morning, i thought about what time i would come back from work today so that i could take a nap before dinner.  then i got up to brush my teeth.  somehow i ended up back in bed and took a nap until 10!  and now, after a tuna melt for lunch, i hear the sleep fairies calling my name again.

going to get some caffeine now.
i just took a dog iq test for smiley, and he scored 124! the average is 120. yay smiley!
is class 4 scary? i'm going whitewater rafting for the first time this sunday. we're taking the middle fork of the american river. i'm not that great of a swimmer so i hope i stay on the raft :)

with my sister back in town, my family took a trip down to the hearst castle in san simeon. we stayed at the sea coast lodge because it was so close to the castle and had pet rooms! smiley had a great time, and we took lots of pictures.

Bender is in town for a few days, and yesterday we brought him to Sausalito where it was 11 degrees warmer than the city! It was a beautiful day for a street fair. Many dogs were out enjoying the sun. A live band played while we hula hooped, and here are the pics to prove it!

i recently moved into a new apartment, and there is a steam bath and jacuzzi in the bathroom. i tried the steam bath last night, and it completely relaxed me. :) just read an article that talks about other benefits. one more day till san diego!
only 3 more days until san diego! we got the $39 deal from southwest, and we're going to stay at a lovely resort on the beach of la jolla. can't wait!

i was walking to trader joe's today and passed by this stereo/tv store that a guy had just come out of.  i saw an old lady coming out behind him and the door was about to slam on her.  it was a natural reflex to run back and grab the door for her.  she held my hand and said "thanks, only a woman would do that"...  that cracked me up.

now my hand smells like her perfume.

me, my dad, kevin, and over 20 thousand other people showed up tonight for the golden state and warriors game tonight. rockets won by 10, and we got to see yao ming's first nba 3 pointer! it was an awesome game :)

just wanted to recommend a brand of tea that i had a while ago and really liked: ahmad tea from london the mango flavored tea was pretty yummy. i had to be strategic about driving to work today since most of the city streets were rampaged by anti-war protestors. i decided to take the freeway which was nice and easy. some folks sat at intersections for 30-40 minutes. i heard that many people were protesting for other issues other than war. i feel like going out there to protest a parking ticket i got the other day!

kelly and i skipped out on work a little early yesterday to go see the bouquet to arts exhibit at the legion of honor she really liked the red-orange arrangements, and we both really liked this purple hydrangea and copper wire display that was an exact representation of the painting behind it. my personal favorite was the life-size harp made out flowers. i wish i had pictures to show, but i left my camera at home yesterday :( the sites and smells of the museum were amazing yesterday.
i saw this picture and it just reminds me of smiley's new "trick":
who knew they made some with smileys on them?
today i got to use one of these machines to measure my lung volumes and stuff. quite an experience.
for those of you who watched the bachelorette, radioalice interviewed russell, and he has a webpage that includes his diary from the show and other factoids.

it's also smiley's 3rd birthday today! :) my neighbor ordered him a doggie bday cake from the three dog bakery, and they did such a wonderful job. we lit some candles and sang to him this morning, hehe. nothing too fancy planned for tonight. i think we're just going to have dinner at home and watch a dvd. kevin has some surprise planned for tomorrow, and i haven't been able to guess what...
smiley's friend came to visit over the weekend. they met up at petsmart and spent the rest of the night at home. you can tell it was a pretty long day for the both of them.

so it turns out that noah indeed has FUS. we went to the vet again yesterday and got him some meds. these next couple of days are pretty critical. my coworker sent me this story about a cat with the same problem.

oh no, poor noah isn't feeling so well today. kevin is taking him to the vet right now. i'm worried he might have feline urinary tract disease because he seems to be in pain and peed in the living room this morning. good thing kevin caught it right away.

chinese new year is tomorrow. that means we're going to have a big feast tonight for dinner. tomorrow brings lots of red envelopes and a day of fasting (my family is vegetarian on new year's day). hope the year of the ram brings everyone much luck, good health, and happiness!

yes! i got my super white prius from a great dealership on geary last night. my salesman was collin who used to be a cable car driver. i highly recommend him because he treats his customers really well. as for that other crap dealership, i posted a couple of reviews on craigslist and ripoffreport. collin also said that toyota would give me a call soon after my purchase so i could tell them about what happened in daly city. he had worked there for a day but quit on the spot because he disagreed with the way they did business. my car is running great! got around 40mpg this morning coming to work, and it was nice smooth ride.
